I live with bipolar, but it does not define me. I try to see it as a gift. All my difficult depressions have helped me be compassionate to others currently suffering. I do community volunteering to help eliminate stigma.

Living with bipolar, I became scared when faced with the challenges of the current pandemic. However, as I read info from reliable sources, and talk to my daughter who is an expert researcher, I see things in a better perspective. Prayer brings comfort. Isolating is lonely.
